17:45.899 --> 17:46.900
What <i>is</i> happening?

17:47.818 --> 17:48.819
What's happening, Clare?

17:48.819 --> 17:52.030
I mean, am I gonna see your--
your mug shot on the eleven-o'clock news?

17:52.656 --> 17:55.450
"Former health care employee
charged with elder assault"?

17:55.450 --> 17:58.036
I mean, Jesus! Who are you?

17:59.037 --> 18:00.122
What do you mean, who am I?

18:00.122 --> 18:02.749
Right now, who the fuck are you, Clare?

18:05.460 --> 18:06.461
I don't know!

18:07.379 --> 18:08.380
Danny!

18:10.007 --> 18:14.303
Maybe this is what happens
when you get exiled from your own daughter

18:14.303 --> 18:18.348
by the person who is supposed
to love, honor, and cherish me!

18:18.348 --> 18:20.225
'Cause I don't feel fucking cherished!

18:20.225 --> 18:21.643
Where's the cherishing?

18:21.643 --> 18:22.644
- Clare--
- No!

18:23.562 --> 18:26.565
You don't know what it fucking feels like
to be kicked out of your own fucking home!

18:27.482 --> 18:31.904
I couldn't spend another night
on Amy's... stupid pullout couch.

18:31.904 --> 18:33.155
[mouthing] What?

18:33.155 --> 18:35.282
I didn't have anywhere else to go!

18:35.282 --> 18:37.743
I'm not like you! Danny, I just--

18:39.328 --> 18:41.955
It's you and Rae, that's it.
I have nobody else.

18:43.832 --> 18:46.793
- And Lucas.
- No, Lucas has me. I don't have him.

18:50.964 --> 18:52.216
I just wanna go home.

18:55.719 --> 18:57.471
I mean, you could put me anywhere.

18:57.471 --> 19:00.641
You can just
shove me in a closet, I don't care.

19:00.641 --> 19:02.267
I just wanna go home.

19:07.272 --> 19:09.274
[sniffles] Ugh.

19:10.400 --> 19:11.401
Okay.

19:17.282 --> 19:18.534
Okay?

19:19.117 --> 19:20.327
[Danny sighs]

19:20.327 --> 19:21.954
We can keep going to therapy.

19:21.954 --> 19:22.955
You know, try to--

19:24.831 --> 19:26.583
try to find our way back to a good place.

19:27.459 --> 19:28.460
Great.

19:29.545 --> 19:30.712
Okay, great.

19:31.547 --> 19:32.548
It's great.

19:33.507 --> 19:37.010
I-- I ju-- I wonder,
uh, about Mel, but, uh--

19:37.010 --> 19:38.011
What about Mel?

19:38.011 --> 19:40.013
Uh, nothing. Nothing. That's great.

19:41.431 --> 19:42.558
Okay.

19:43.433 --> 19:44.434
[mouthing] All right.

19:46.520 --> 19:47.729
Oh, um...

19:48.522 --> 19:50.566
you might wanna
change the sheets in our bed.

19:51.233 --> 19:53.735
Rae was having a threesome on it.

19:56.446 --> 19:57.447
DANNY:
Wait, what?

20:00.909 --> 20:02.703
Uh, chapel's not open yet. Sorry.

20:05.330 --> 20:07.624
Hey. How you doing?

20:08.333 --> 20:09.543
- O-kay. Okay.
- Yeah.

20:10.794 --> 20:11.795
Um...

20:12.337 --> 20:15.632
Uh, J-- Joel and I
went to high school together.

20:15.632 --> 20:16.633
This is Jess.

20:16.633 --> 20:17.634
My, um...

20:18.468 --> 20:19.469
husband.

20:20.888 --> 20:23.599
So I brought the... guest book.
What can I do?

20:26.518 --> 20:27.895
Nothing.

20:27.895 --> 20:29.104
[softly] Okay.

20:34.109 --> 20:37.112
♪

21:04.097 --> 21:07.100
♪

21:24.785 --> 21:26.787
[baby crying]

21:30.707 --> 21:31.708
Fuck!

21:31.708 --> 21:34.711
[baby continues crying]

21:41.301 --> 21:42.302
It's okay.

21:43.428 --> 21:44.429
It's okay.

21:45.180 --> 21:47.057
Don't let it stop you. Keep going.

21:47.558 --> 21:48.809
<i>She's okay.</i>

21:48.809 --> 21:50.102
<i>Babies cry.</i>

21:50.102 --> 21:52.104
<i>Don't-- Don't let it stop you.</i>

21:53.146 --> 21:56.358
♪

22:09.496 --> 22:11.957
You hungry? You want something to eat?

22:17.045 --> 22:18.046
He didn't show.

22:18.755 --> 22:19.923
[sniffling]

22:19.923 --> 22:20.924
Dad.

22:22.134 --> 22:25.137
♪

22:28.390 --> 22:31.810
<i>♪ Paper roses ♪</i>

22:32.936 --> 22:36.815
<i>♪ Paper roses ♪</i>

22:37.357 --> 22:43.363
[singing along]
<i>♪ But like a big red rose
that's made of paper ♪</i>

22:45.657 --> 22:51.663
<i>♪ There isn't any sweetness
in your heart ♪</i>

22:53.290 --> 22:54.666
<i>♪ Paper roses... ♪</i>

22:55.083 --> 22:57.711
Do you remember
I used to sing this to you?

22:59.963 --> 23:01.173
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

23:04.426 --> 23:05.844
It's gonna be okay.

23:09.014 --> 23:10.015
[sniffling]

23:10.766 --> 23:11.975
The doctor said a year.

23:15.103 --> 23:16.647
Doctors aren't always right.

23:18.857 --> 23:20.067
WOMAN:
Frances Pierce?

23:22.319 --> 23:23.320
[Frankie clears throat]

23:24.112 --> 23:26.949
FRANKIE:
If they give you any trouble,
you just tell them who you are.

23:28.534 --> 23:29.868
Tell them you're my daughter.

23:33.121 --> 23:36.124
♪

23:40.796 --> 23:41.797
CLARE:
<i>Dear Sam.</i>

23:42.506 --> 23:44.508
<i>What the fuck? What the fuck?</i>

23:45.676 --> 23:48.387
<i>What the fuck does it take
for me to get you an answer?</i>

23:49.221 --> 23:50.848
<i>Since you offered me the column,</i>

23:50.848 --> 23:55.644
<i>I have been wondering
who am I to give advice to anyone?</i>

23:57.229 --> 23:58.230
<i>Wondering...</i>

23:59.231 --> 24:00.440
<i>who am I at all?</i>

24:02.526 --> 24:04.361
<i>The question beats in me like a drum:</i>

24:05.153 --> 24:09.783
<i>Who am I? Who am I? Who am I?</i>

24:10.701 --> 24:14.246
<i>How did I get so far
from the person I wanted to be?</i>

24:14.246 --> 24:17.124
<i>The writer my mom believed I could be.</i>

24:20.919 --> 24:24.882
LITTLE CLARE:
<i>Clare Marie Pierce
lives in the wilds of Fall Creek</i>

24:24.882 --> 24:26.175
<i>with her mom and brother.</i>

24:27.217 --> 24:29.928
<i>She loves reading and writing stories,</i>

24:29.928 --> 24:34.892
<i>and her dream is to live
in New York and London and Orlando.</i>

24:36.476 --> 24:38.604
<i>She's an accomplished writer.</i>

24:44.651 --> 24:45.944
CLARE:
<i>But I do know who I am.</i>

24:48.363 --> 24:50.657
<i>When all else fails
and nothing makes sense,</i>

24:53.452 --> 24:55.037
<i>I am always three things.</i>

24:57.623 --> 24:59.041
<i>I am my mother's daughter.</i>

25:03.670 --> 25:05.172
<i>I am my daughter's mother.</i>

25:09.384 --> 25:11.220
<i>And I am an accomplished writer.</i>

25:13.388 --> 25:15.057
<i>Even if I haven't accomplished it yet.</i>

25:17.726 --> 25:18.936
<i>So yes, Sam.</i>

25:19.686 --> 25:20.687
<i>Yes.</i>

25:22.564 --> 25:23.565
<i>Yours,</i>

25:24.816 --> 25:25.817
<i>Sugar.</i>

25:34.243 --> 25:40.249
<i>♪ I thought that
you would be a perfect lover ♪</i>

25:41.917 --> 25:47.047
<i>♪ You seemed
so full of sweetness at the start ♪</i>

25:49.800 --> 25:55.806
<i>♪ But like a big red rose
that's made of paper ♪</i>

25:57.349 --> 26:03.355
<i>♪ There isn't any sweetness
in your heart ♪</i>

26:04.356 --> 26:07.359
<i>♪ Paper roses ♪</i>

26:08.193 --> 26:11.196
<i>♪ Paper roses ♪</i>

26:12.030 --> 26:17.703
<i>♪ Oh, how real those roses seem to be ♪</i>

26:19.705 --> 26:23.542
<i>♪ But they're only ♪</i>

26:23.542 --> 26:27.588
<i>♪ Imitation ♪</i>

26:28.338 --> 26:33.010
<i>♪ Like your imitation love for me ♪</i>
